"'''Heartbeat'''" is a song by Nigerian singer [[Nneka (singer)|Nneka]]. It was released in 2008 as a single from her second studio album ''No Longer at Ease'', as well as her third studio album ''[[Concrete Jungle (Nneka album)|Concrete Jungle]]''. A 2010 EP release of the song features American rapper [[Nas]]. The song was remixed by English [[electronic music]] duo [[Chase & Status]] and included on the "new edition" of their debut studio album, ''[[More than Alot]]''. The remix of the song was sampled in [[Rita Ora]]'s 2012 song "[[R.I.P. (Rita Ora song)|R.I.P.]]".

== Background ==
The original release of the song was written by Nneka Egbuna (Nneka) and produced by DJ Farhot, and released as a single in 2008.<ref name="liner notes">{{cite AV media notes|others=[[Nneka (singer)|Nneka]]|title=Heartbeat|year=2008|type=Liner Notes|publisher=Yo Mama's Recording Company}}</ref> A music video was released to promote the single. An EP for the song was released on 5 October 2010, featuring American rapper Nas.<ref name="iTunes">{{cite web|title=Heartbeat - EP by Nneka|work=[[iTunes Store]]|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/heartbeat-ep/394862146|accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref>

The song charted on release in Portugal, Germany, and Austria. In 2009, the song charted in the [[UK Singles Chart]] at position 20. The song has also charted in France and the Netherlands.

